entries.femaleVariant: Good evening, Night City. We begin with, uh… uh…
Panic has saturated the market... This latest slump has led to losses in excess of 500 billion eurodollars.
Following another attack on Arasaka's Night City HQ, the, uh, Japanese goliath has plummeted by 17 percent. And we should expect that slide to continue, say analysts.
According to a statement from the NCPD, the attack was carried out by a group of nomads who pierced the tower via a maglev railway tunnel.
In light of these events, I have only one recommendation, my friends. Sell.
We begin tonight with... with a look at the stock market. As always.
Arasaka CEO, Yorinobu Arasaka, has since evacuated his Night City office for Tokyo.
Sell now, while you still can.
